<p>Downtown Springfield's urban core presents opportunities for solar installations on flat commercial roofs and modern residential buildings. The McKnight and Pine Point neighborhoods, with their mix of older and newer construction, benefit from energy efficiency upgrades that pair well with solar installations. East Springfield's residential areas often have ideal roof orientations for solar, while Bay and Brightwood neighborhoods may require more careful system sizing due to varying home sizes and energy needs.</p>

